						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 96 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp before the image of Sūryadēva and an endowment of 5 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for the daily offering to the deity, in the temple of Tāntōṉṟi-Āḷvār at Vāḷaiyūr, by the <hi rend="italic">ūrār</hi> of Kumaṇamaṅgalam.</p>						

